"title": "5043: names, significance of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5043",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Labels that idenitfy individuals. They may also denote aspects of character or reputation.</p>\n<h2>A name may reflect an individual's nature</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:25\">1SA 25:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:5\">GEN 17:5</a> <em>“Abraham” means “father of many”</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:27-Gen32:29\">GEN 32:27–32:29</a> <em>“Israel” means “he struggles with God”</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:14\">EXO 34:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:9\">MRK 5:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:30\">LUK 8:30</a></p>\n<h3>Additional names or nicknames</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:17\">MRK 3:17</a></strong> <em>In NT times an additional name or surname reflecting someone's character was sometimes appended to the given name.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:15\">LUK 6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:42\">JHN 1:42</a> <em>“Cephas” and “Peter” mean “rock” in Aramaic and Greek respectively</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:36\">ACT 4:36</a></p>\n<h2>A name may indicate an individual's reputation and standing in the community</h2>\n<h3>A good name indicates a good reputation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:1\">PRO 22:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:4\">PRO 3:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:7\">PRO 10:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:1\">ECC 7:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:3\">SNG 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>A bad name indicates a bad reputation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh6:13\">NEH 6:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:13-Deut22:19\">DEU 22:13–22:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:9-Prov25:10\">PRO 25:9–25:10</a></p>\n<h2>Survival of one's name is important</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:9-Ruth4:10\">RUT 4:9–4:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:15-Gen48:16\">GEN 48:15–48:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:1-Num27:4\">NUM 27:1–27:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:7-Deut25:9\">DEU 25:7–25:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:18\">2SA 18:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job18:17-Job18:19\">JOB 18:17–18:19</a></p>\n<h3>Preservation of a name indicates divine blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:4-Isa56:5\">ISA 56:4–56:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:1-Gen12:3\">GEN 12:1–12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:9\">2SA 7:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:8\">1CH 17:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:47\">1KI 1:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:22\">ISA 66:22</a></p>\n<h2>Obliteration of a name is associated with death</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:19\">JER 11:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:24\">DEU 7:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:14\">DEU 9:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:7\">2SA 14:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:27\">2KI 14:27</a></p>\n<h2>Obliteration of a name is often linked with divine judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps9:5-Ps9:6\">PSA 9:5–9:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:20\">DEU 29:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:13\">PSA 109:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:22-Isa14:23\">ISA 14:22–14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:18-Isa48:19\">ISA 48:18–48:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:14\">NAM 1:14</a></p>\n<h2>Bearing someone's name indicates ownership or identification</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:3-Rev22:4\">REV 22:3–22:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:21\">EXO 23:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:14\">2CH 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:10\">DEU 28:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:6-Isa43:7\">ISA 43:6–43:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:9\">JER 14:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:18-Dan9:19\">DAN 9:18–9:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:12\">REV 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:1\">REV 14:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:4\">REV 22:4</a></p>\n<h2>God knows his people by name</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:1\">ISA 43:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:12\">EXO 33:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:17\">EXO 33:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:3\">ISA 45:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:1\">ISA 49:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:3\">JHN 10:3</a></p>",
